      "title": "Sri Lanka NBRO issues landslide evacuation alert amid high rainfall, flood risks",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka National Building Research Organization (NBRO) has issued red alert, asking people to evacuate due to possible landslides after several areas in the country due to the prevailing heavy rains, the Disaster Management Centre said.",
        "Areas in Kalutara and Ratnapura districts have been included in the red alert while some area in the same districts along with Galle have been included in level two risk.",
        "Meanwhile the irrigation department has issued flood warnings residents around Kalu Ganga (river) due",
        "to a considerable rainfall been occurred in upstream catchment areas of Kuda Ganga Sub Basin of Kalu",
        "\u201cBy analyzing the current rainfall situation and river water levels of Hydrological Stations in Kuda Ganga,",
        "there is a possibility of occurring a minor flood situation in low-line areas of Kuda Ganga valley situated in",
        "Palinda Nuwara and Bulathsinhala D/S Divisions,\u201d Irrigation department in a statement said.",
        "\u201cIt is requested to pay high attention in this regards by the residents in those area and vehicle drivers",
        "Disaster Management centre said, the water levels of Gin river, Attanagalu Oya and Kelani river are also",
        "rising and asked the residents in low lying areas around the river areas to be vigilant due to possibilities"
      ],
